SIMPLE: intemperateness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intemperateness
<hw>In*tem`per*ate*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state
of being intemperate; excessive indulgence of any appetite or passion;
<as>as, <ex>intemperateness</ex> in eating or drinking</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Severity of weather; inclemency.</def>
<rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By unseasonable weather, by <qex>intemperateness</qex> of the air
or meteors.</q> <rj><qau>Sir M. Hale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intemperature</ent>⟦br⟧
